Brilliant Color & Stunning Image Quality 

The Pen Display 16 is the industry's first 16-inch 4K OLED pen display. It is 10-bit and delivers 1.07 billion colors, giving enhanced color reproduction from deep blacks to vibrant highlights. The screen's resolution is 3840 x 2160, and it has a high contrast ratio of 100,000:1. 
Preloaded Color Spaces for Convenience 

These five common color spaces used across various industries are pre-calibrated in the Pen Display 16: Adobe RGB: 98%, P3-D65: 98%, sRGB: 99%, REC 2020: 82%, REC: 709 99%. This allows you to view your work as intended without requiring color calibration of the display, so you can start creating right out of the box. 
Super AG Etching Display 

The specially designed display surface, Xencelabs' Super AG Etching Display, significantly reduces distracting glare and gives excellent clarity in brightly lit environments or rooms with overhead ceiling lights, providing a clear and uninterrupted drawing experience. 
Optically Bonded Screen 

The screen of the Pen Display 16 is optically bonded, eliminating parallax and producing a bright, clear image with no "sparkling" effect to distract or tire eyes. 
Previous page
Single Cable USB-C Connectivity 
A single USB-C Alt mode enabled cable can link the Pen Display 16 to a computer. This setup offers an uncluttered connection and a comfortable display position, ideal for working on the go. 
Learn More 
Inspiration is Everywhere 
The included Carrying Case was made to be the perfect on-the-go partner for your Pen Display 16. It holds all included accessories, the pen display, and a small laptop. 
Learn More 
Next page
Fluid, Accurate, Responsive Pen Strokes 
Finely Tuned Pressure Curve 

The pressure curve has an initial activation force of 3g and ranges to 500g. This allows for delicate strokes as well as strong, bold lines and everything in between. Thanks to a panel of artists who provided pressure data, the pressure curve has been meticulously tuned, and pen response is adjustable to match any drawing style. Whether heavy or light handed, the pen provides control, sensitivity, and precision. 
Smooth Drawing Experience 

The Pen Display 16 provides beautiful pen control thanks to its etched surface texture, thanks to Xencelabs' Super AG Etching Display. This allows the hand to glide smoothly across the screen, and the friction of the pen nib against the screen provides a traditional pen-and-paper-like drawing experience. 
Streamlined, Ergonomic Design 
Previous page
Two Pens with Case 
Different pen sizes are catered to individual preferences. Both have a built-in eraser and can be assigned to separate settings per application. 
Learn More 
Silence is Golden 
Aluminum back housing ensures rapid heat dissipation without the need of fans, preventing overheating and allowing for more comfortable creation. 
Learn More 
Symmetrical Design 
The symmetrical, streamlined, and ergonomic design of the Pen Display 16 allows for landscape and portrait modes, accommodating various working setups and formats. 
Learn More 
Next page
Adaptable to Artist Preferences 
Previous page
Virtual Tablet Mode 
Virtual Tablet Mode allows creatives to use the Xencelabs Pen and Pen Display 16 to select and control objects on another display. 
Learn More 
Simple, Clear Driver Interface 
The Xencelabs driver is modern and intuitive. The settings panel makes it easy to customize more. With regular updates, it always feels up-to-date and reliable. 
Learn More 
Highly Compatible & Adaptable 
Highly compatible with the devices you need it to. It supports Windows 7 or later, Mac OS X 10.12 or later, and Linux. It also supports a variety of different software applications.
